# Trivy CVE allowlist. Each line is either:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN exp:YYYY-MM-DD     (with expiration — recommended)
# A blank entry never expires. Add a date so we revisit allowlisted CVEs
# instead of letting them sit forever.
#
# Add an entry only after you have:
#   1. Read the advisory and the affected version range.
#   2. Confirmed the vulnerable code path is unreachable in this app
#      (or that the upstream has no fix and you have mitigations).
#   3. Documented the reasoning in the commit that adds the entry.
#
# Empty for now — start clean and add entries as needed.
